Ticket — “Tags CRUD Page”

(Epic 7 – Tags & Settings)

This task builds the small page where you create, rename, and delete tags that get attached to transactions and recurring rules.

Goal	Give the user a quick, friction-free UI to manage the tag list.



⸻

1 Responsibilities of TagsPage.vue

Feature	Details / UI Element
List tags	Simple table (or list) showing name, usage count (optional)
Create tag	Dialog or inline text field + Add button
Rename tag	Pencil icon → inline edit OR dialog
Delete tag	Trash icon → confirm dialog; handle “tag in use” error
Loading state	Linear progress on first load / mutations
Snackbar feedback	Success / error toasts via useSnackbar()


⸻

2 Component hierarchy

TagsPage.vue
 ├─ TagTable.vue           (v-data-table or v-list)
 ├─ TagFormDialog.vue      (Add / Rename)
 └─ ConfirmDialog.vue      (Delete confirm)



5 Validation & UX

Scenario	Behaviour
Duplicate name	Store/API returns 409 → show red snackbar “Tag name already exists.”
Name blank	Dialog shows “Required” rule, save disabled
Tag attached to transactions	API responds 400 “tag in use” → snackbar error


⸻

6 Acceptance Criteria
	1.	Page loads and shows all tags from backend.
	2.	Adding a tag updates list without refresh; snackbar “Tag added”.
	3.	Renaming reflects immediately; duplicate handled gracefully.
	4.	Delete shows confirm; if tag unused, it disappears; if in use, error toast.
	5.	All actions show/clear loading states; no console errors.
	6.	Unit/E2E tests pass (add, edit, delete happy-path).

When those behaviours work end-to-end, the “Tags CRUD page” ticket is complete.